---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Avatar
description: an avatar indicator showing a user photo or user text
---

{% from "components/avatar/macro.njk" import avatar %}
{% from "components/avatar-text/macro.njk" import avatarText %}

<h2>Initials</h2>
<p>
  {% call avatar({ label: "Jane Smith" }) %}
    {{ avatarText({ text: "JS" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call avatar({ label: "Kofi Tetteh" }) %}
    {{ avatarText({ text: "KT" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call avatar({ label: "Priya Patel" }) %}
    {{ avatarText({ text: "PP" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
</p>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<p>The outer <code>Avatar</code> carries <code>role="img"</code> plus
  an <code>aria-label</code> like "Jane Smith" — so screen readers
  announce the person, not the letters of the initials. The inner
  <code>AvatarText</code> is <code>aria-hidden</code> by default so
  it is not read a second time.</p>
